¢G"h<?php exit; ?>a:2:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":24:{s:2:"ID";i:11536;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2025-02-08 22:36:28";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2025-02-08 22:36:28";s:12:"post_content";s:1760:"We're thrilled to complete the spotlight of the creative team for <em>Rebecca Roman Redd at the Most Dangerous Hour</em> with Tonia E. Anderson, who played Priscilla Margot Saunders. Tonia last appeared inÂ <em>Rizing</em> with Flux, and we were thrilled to have her return in full comic fabulousness for the iconic Priscilla<em>. </em>We asked Tonia a few questions based on Montserrat Mendez's dizzyingly funny and brilliant new play, which you can learn more about <a href="https://www.fluxtheatre.org/2025/01/rebecca-roman-redd-at-the-most-dangerous-hour/">here</a>.

<strong>On a scale of 1 to werewolf, how close of a relationship do you have with the moon</strong>?

Just call me Luna, baby.

<strong>Finish the sentence: the best kind of tart is a ____ tart.</strong>

Ginger-apple-cranberry.

<strong>Who did you end up stuck with when the pandemic first struck...and how did that go?</strong>

The love of my life and I'd call it a distillation.

<strong>Tonia E. Anderson</strong> (she/her): Born in South Carolina, polished at Harvard, distilled by New York City. Toni A. continues her journey to becoming the artist of her dreams, acting, writing, and occasionally directing to capture some of her southern, army brat, craft maven, sci-fi-geek-girl experiences for the boards. She has challenged her artistic boundaries most recently by producing for and acting in a short film, <em>The Right One</em>. toniaanderson.net

